### Node Position Calculation

```python
# Center: (720, 480)
# Suppliers (top arc, radius=300):
angle = math.pi * (5/6 - i * (2/3) / (n-1))  # 150° to 30°
x = 720 + 300 * cos(angle) - 100
y = 480 + 300 * sin(angle) - 45

# Customers/Partners (right side):
x = 1160
y = 200 + i * 150

# Others (bottom arc, radius=320):
angle = -math.pi * (1/6 + i * (2/3) / (n-1))  # -30° to -150°
x = 720 + 320 * cos(angle) - 100
y = 480 + 320 * sin(angle) - 45
```

