## Step 6: Upload to GCS & Track in Neo4j

After generating the files locally, save them to cloud storage and create a tracking record.

### CLI Command: save-blog-post

```bash
python -m apps.cli.main save-blog-post \
  --entity {ENTITY_ID} \
  --perspective {PERSPECTIVE} \
  --chart-type {CHART_TYPE} \
  --title "{CHINESE_TITLE}" \
  --ticker {STOCK_TICKER} \
  --svg {entity}_{perspective}.svg \
  --article {entity}_{perspective}_article.md
```

### Example:

```bash
# Save Google supply chain blog post
python -m apps.cli.main save-blog-post \
  --entity google \
  --perspective supply_chain \
  --chart-type N_TIER_NODE_MAP \
  --title "Google AI 帝國的供應鏈版圖" \
  --ticker GOOGL \
  --svg google_supply_chain.svg \
  --article google_supply_chain_article.md

# Save Google AI business blog post
python -m apps.cli.main save-blog-post \
  --entity google \
  --perspective ai_business \
  --chart-type STACK_PYRAMID \
  --title "Google AI 帝國全景：從 Gemini 到 TPU" \
  --ticker GOOGL \
  --svg google_ai_business.svg \
  --article google_ai_business_article.md
```

### Files are uploaded to:
- SVG: `gs://graphfolio-articles/blog/svg/{entity}_{perspective}.svg`
- Article: `gs://graphfolio-articles/blog/md/{entity}_{perspective}.md`

