## Future: Cloud Storage Integration

For production deployment, articles and visualizations should be stored in cloud databases:

### Recommended Storage Architecture

```
┌─────────────────┐
│   Neo4j Aura    │ ← Metadata: entity_id, title, created_at, references
└────────┬────────┘
         │
         ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│  GCS Bucket     │ ← Files: SVG, Markdown articles
│ graphfolio-     │
│  articles/      │
│  ├── svg/       │
│  └── md/        │
└─────────────────┘
```

### Neo4j Schema for Articles
```cypher
(:BlogPost {
  id: "google_supply_chain_2024",
  entity_id: "google",
  title: "Google AI 帝國的供應鏈版圖",
  svg_gcs_path: "gs://graphfolio-articles/svg/google_supply_chain.svg",
  article_gcs_path: "gs://graphfolio-articles/md/google_supply_chain.md",
  created_at: datetime(),
  word_count: 1200,
  entities_count: 10
})
```

### Deduplication Query
```cypher
MATCH (b:BlogPost {entity_id: $ticker})
WHERE b.created_at > datetime() - duration({days: 30})
RETURN b.title, b.created_at
```
If results exist within 30 days → Skip generation

### Upload to GCS
```python
from services.article_storage import GCSArticleStorage

storage = GCSArticleStorage(config)
storage.upload_file("google_supply_chain.svg", "svg/google_supply_chain.svg")
storage.upload_file("google_supply_chain_article.md", "md/google_supply_chain.md")
```

