## MCP API Server

The blog post tools are also available as an HTTP API for remote access.

### Local Development

```bash
# Run the API server locally
python -m mcp.servers.blog_post_api

# Or with uvicorn
uvicorn mcp.servers.blog_post_api:app --port 8001 --reload
```

### Deploy to Google Cloud Run

```bash
# Build and deploy
gcloud run deploy blog-post-api \
  --source . \
  --dockerfile Dockerfile.blog-api \
  --region us-central1 \
  --set-env-vars "NEO4J_URI=$NEO4J_URI,NEO4J_USER=$NEO4J_USER,NEO4J_PASSWORD=$NEO4J_PASSWORD,GCS_BUCKET_NAME=graphfolio-articles" \
  --allow-unauthenticated
```

### API Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/` | GET | Service info |
| `/health` | GET | Health check |
| `/tools/list_blog_posts` | POST | List blog posts |
| `/tools/check_duplicate` | POST | Check for duplicates |
| `/tools/suggest_perspective` | POST | Get suggestions |
| `/tools/save_blog_post` | POST | Save blog post |
| `/tools/get_entity_summary` | POST | Get entity summary |
| `/mcp/tools/list` | GET | List MCP tools |
| `/mcp/tools/call` | POST | MCP-compatible tool call |

### Example API Call

```bash
# List blog posts
curl -X POST https://YOUR-SERVICE.run.app/tools/list_blog_posts \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"entity_id": "google"}'

# Suggest perspectives
curl -X POST https://YOUR-SERVICE.run.app/tools/suggest_perspective \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"entity_id": "google"}'
```
